Freelander: A term for a person or group seeking political/personal freedom through [[emigration]] to and [[settlement]] of open land.  The term is primarily used in a fictional or speculative sense of freelanders emigrating from earth to other bodies in the [[solar system]].  Inherent to the idea of being a freelander is the idea of being independent and [[self-sufficient]].  Freelanders are typically described as associating with like-minded individuals, but different freelander groups may be quite different from one another (i.e., [[libertarian]] vs. [[authoritarian]], [[capitalist]] vs. [[communist]]).

Freelander: A model manufactured by the [[Land Rover]] company. A full time [[4x4]] on and off-road vehicle which saw the turn-around of fortunes that were eventually to save the marque. Originally Land Rover was part of the British [[Rover]] corporation.  It became part of [[BWM]] in the 1990s when they purchased Rover before becomuing part of [[Ford]]'s PAG (Premier Automotive Group).

